            "text/markdown": "In the example above:\n\n- `simple_decorator` is the **outer function**. It takes `func` (which is `say_hello` in this case) as an argument.\n- `wrapper` is the **inner function**. It contains the code that runs *before* (`print(\"Something is happening before...\")`) and *after* (`print(\"Something is happening after...\")`) the original function `func()` is called.\n- `simple_decorator` returns the `wrapper` function.\n- When we manually apply the decorator with `decorated_say_hello = simple_decorator(say_hello)`, `decorated_say_hello` becomes the `wrapper` function.\n- Calling `decorated_say_hello()` actually executes the `wrapper` function, which in turn calls the original `say_hello()` function between the extra print statements.\n"
