        "%%markdown\n",
        "### Using the `@` Syntax\n",
        "\n",
        "Python provides a more convenient and readable way to apply decorators using the `@` syntax. This is just syntactic sugar for the manual application we saw earlier (`decorated_function = decorator(original_function)`). Placing `@decorator_name` directly above a function definition is equivalent to manually applying the decorator to that function."
      ],
