        "    - `time.time()` records the start time.\n",
        "    - `result = func(*args, **kwargs)` calls the original `complex_operation` function with the received arguments. The `time.sleep()` inside `complex_operation` simulates work, making the timing noticeable. The return value of `complex_operation` is captured in the `result` variable.\n",
        "    - `time.time()` records the end time after the original function finishes.\n",
        "    - The difference between end time and start time is calculated as `run_time`.\n",
